The paper deals with the extension of answer-set programming with weight constraints, which is a topic related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and logic in computer science (cs.LO). The use of treewidth to identify tractable fragments is a technique from algorithms and data structures (cs.DS), while the application of this technique to programs or formulas falls under databases (cs.DB) and computational complexity (cs.CC).
